Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light red-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '88' and another number. Name Euanor. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 091.37.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (150)
